05/03/2007
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- A team of experts from the European Commission (EC) kicks off a five-day visit to Montenegro on Monday (March 5th) to assess the country's judicial sector, as well as policies related to freedoms and security.
Its findings will be crucial to the EC's future stance on the level of progress achieved by Montenegro in reforming the judicial and security sectors, strengthening of administrative capacities and combating crime and corruption.
(Vijesti - 04/03/07;
Pobjeda - 03/03/07)
